Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat the @sesame oil{20%ml} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Fry the @sliced mushrooms{120%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Boil the @egg noodle nest{125%g}, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and @sugar snap peas{80%g} to the mushrooms. Fry, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir through the @gochujang paste{30%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @ketjap manis{50%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @honey{15%g} and a splash of water.

> TIP: Pop hardened honey into hot water for 1 min.

Bring to the boil. Add the cooked noodles. Toss to combine, ~{1%minute}.

Serve your noodles in #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{40%g} to finish. Enjoy!